I have successfully generated candidate stimuli, computed the EIG for each against the current cognitive models, and selected the 20 most informative pairs. 

The selected design actively pits sequences with extreme class imbalances (like all heads or all tails) against highly alternating, balanced sequences. This targets the primary split in the existing model set, where the prevailing models (`inner_loop_model`, `iter1_candidate2`) hypothesize that people perceive high imbalance as random, which starkly contrasts with the classic alternation and balanced-prototype models.

The resulting assets have been saved:
- `design/stimuli.json` (20 stimuli pairs, EIG range 0.3900 - 0.5067)
- `design/design_rationale.md` (Explaining the discriminatory basis)
